sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2036024
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: RBS-iLDH-TT-pRM-RBS-beta-galactosidase,iLDH are lactic dehydrogenase,while beta-galactosidase can transfer lactose into monosaccharide.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Zhangyu Cheng
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: iLDH are from the Registry and beta-galactosidase coding gene are referred to pUC119 commerial vector and synthesised by IDT.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: beta-galactosidase coding gene are alpha domain of laz,it functions only in E.coli strain which contains lacZ operon.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2036021
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Zhangyu Cheng
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The circuit are redesign of bacteriaphage lambda operon.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It is a tri-stable system with a certain threshold and it functions as a basic gene expression toolkit for two input and three related output.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2036022
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Zhangyu Cheng
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: placm is a mutant lac promoter which has been deleted a illegal restriction site. pRE, Cro, CII are from bacteriaphage lambda.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: With this two pormoter design, lactose an induce downstream gene's expression,and CII protein can form a positive feedback by activate pRE so, the circuit can fastly reach a stable state for Cro expression.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2036023
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Zhangyu Cheng
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: patp2 are from Corynebacterium glutamicum ATCC 13032, CI, CIII and pR are all from bacteriaphage lambda.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: patp2 are active within pH7~9, so CI will be produced to inhibit pR thus we can regulate CIII's expression by PH level.
